The 26-year-old man and 47-year-old women were held in Newham, while the 50-year-old woman was arrested in Redbridge.

DCI Adam Lowe from the Sapphire Command said: 'These arrests are part of an investigation into rape and serious sexual assault carried out by a group of men in Newham and the wider east London area. Our enquiries continue.

'I would urge anyone who has been a victim of this type of offence or who believes they have any information to please contact police on 0208 217 6531 or Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111'.

